WEBVTT

00:03:57.135 --> 00:04:00.527
and there are nine of these homes
around a central courtyard.

00:04:00.551 --> 00:04:01.720
This one's mine,

00:04:02.450 --> 00:04:04.236
and this one is Spencer and Sheila's.

00:04:04.935 --> 00:04:07.572
The thing that makes this building
uniquely cohousing

00:04:07.596 --> 00:04:08.878
are not the homes,

00:04:09.743 --> 00:04:11.610
but rather, what happens here --

00:04:12.430 --> 00:04:16.255
the social interactions that happen
in and around that central courtyard.

00:04:16.908 --> 00:04:18.594
When I look across the courtyard,

00:04:18.618 --> 00:04:20.633
I look forward to see Spencer and Sheila.

00:04:20.657 --> 00:04:22.693
In fact, every morning,
this is what I see,

00:04:22.717 --> 00:04:25.934
Spencer waving at me furiously
as we're making our breakfasts.

00:04:27.064 --> 00:04:29.554
From our homes, we look down
into the courtyard,